<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Psychology
242<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><b><span style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Project
1:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Survey<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>For this project you will design, conduct, and report a
survey.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Your survey will test a
hypothesis about a relationship between two variables.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">   </span>The project has three items to be turned
in:</p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><u>Project
     1a – Turn in survey</u> (Turn in 1 copy for grading, plus 1 copy for
     administering)<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><u><o:p></o:p></u></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><u>Project
     1b – Turn in data</u> (Using the “digital drop box” in Blackboard)<span
     style='mso-tab-count:1'>    </span><u><o:p></o:p></u></li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'><u>Project
     1c – Lab report for survey due</u> (in APA style)<span style='mso-tab-count:
     1'>    </span><span style='mso-tab-count:1'>            </span><span
     style='mso-tab-count:1'>            </span></li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Project 1a is a group project – each group will develop one
survey.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You will also work as a group
to collect the data and create a data file containing all the responses to your
survey (Project 1b).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You may also
collaborate with the other members of your group for data analysis (although
you may also choose to analyze the data yourself).<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>The final write-up of the results of the survey (Project 1c) is
an individual assignment.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Project 1a:<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Survey Instrument<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Each group will create one survey.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>On the day that the survey is due, your group should bring <b>two
copies</b> to turn in (along with a cover sheet with all group members’ names
on each copy).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Your survey should be
formatted to fit on 3 pages or less (not including the cover sheet) and should
have your group number at the top of the first page.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>In addition, each group member should turn in a peer evaluation
form along with Project 1a.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You may
turn in the peer evaluation form separately by placing it under my door to
increase confidentiality.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Your survey should test a hypothesis about the relationship
between two variables.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The hypotheses
you will test are as follows:</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'>Even numbered Groups:<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>People who like pets are more introverted
than those who do not.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.5in'>Odd numbered Groups:<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>People who are “night owls” are more
extroverted than “morning people.” </p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p style='margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt'>There are many existing scales that
measure introversion and extroversion.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>You will probably want to look up one of these in a textbook, journal,
or other source and select items from it to measure this variable.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>For the second variable in your hypothesis,
you will probably have to make up your own questions. </p>

<p style='margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p style='margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt'>You should have at least 5
questions for each scale in your survey, and 10 questions each would be even
better.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You should also remember to
reverse the scale on half of your questions - in other words, for half of the
questions on your introversion/extroversion scale, &quot;yes&quot; or strong
agreement should indicate introversion, and for half &quot;yes&quot; or strong
agreement should indicate extroversion.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>The reason for doing this is to prevent response bias from affecting
your results.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If someone just always
tends to answer &quot;no&quot; to any question, for example, that could bias
the results of your survey if all the questions were worded so that
&quot;yes&quot; indicated extroversion.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;
mso-bidi-language:AR-SA'><br clear=all style='page-break-before:always'>
</span>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Project 1b:<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Turn in Data<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>By the due date listed in the syllabus, your group must
place a copy of your survey data in the Blackboard digital drop box (under
Student Tools).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This should be an Excel
file or SPSS data file in which you have entered all of the data from your
survey.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The filename should clearly
identify your group, such as “group1-survey-data.xls” if it is an Excel file
for example.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<span style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;
mso-bidi-language:AR-SA'><br clear=all style='page-break-before:always'>
</span>

<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><b><span
style='font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt'>Project 1c:<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Survey Lab Report<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Project 1c is an individual assignment in which you will
report the results of your survey.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This
lab report must be written in APA style.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Because it is a lab report rather than a full paper, however, the
introduction does not need to include a literature review.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You are required to include at least one
reference, but it can be an Intro Psych textbook or a source from which you
obtained items for your survey.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The
entire lab report should be in 12-point font double-spaced, and you are limited
to 10 pages including the appendix.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>(This is <b>not</b> a minimum!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>It does not have to be exactly 10 pages – it just can not be any longer
than that.)</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Some points to keep in mind when writing your paper:</p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Your
     introduction should clearly state your hypothesis and explain it.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Method</li>
 <ul style='margin-top:0in' type=circle>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>Include
      the subsections: Participants, design, materials, procedure</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>Your
      method section should clearly describe the scales that measure each of
      the variables from your hypothesis.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
      </span></li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>You
      should describe the precautions you took to prevent response bias
      (tending to always say “yes” or always say “no”) and other biases such as
      social desirability.</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>You
      should identify the source of any questions or scales you took from
      previous research, and provide any relevant information about the
      reliability and validity of those scales in the method section.</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>Include
      your survey questions in an appendix</li>
 </ul>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Results</li>
 <ul style='margin-top:0in' type=circle>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>Your
      results section should include a measure of the reliability of your
      survey</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>Your
      results section should describe how you translated the responses on the
      survey form to numerical data, and how you combined the questions of each
      scale to create a single measure for each variable</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>You
      should provide means and standard deviations (or standard errors) for
      each variable you have defined</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>You
      should use a correlation to test your hypothesis about the relationship
      of the two variables</li>
 </ul>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Discussion</li>
 <ul style='margin-top:0in' type=circle>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>You
      should discuss the reliability and validity of the measures in your
      survey</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>You
      should state whether your hypothesis was confirmed</li>
  <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level2 lfo6;tab-stops:list 1.0in'>You
      should offer possible interpretations that could explain why the
      hypothesis was or was not confirmed.</li>
 </ul>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

